  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening the Collective Protection and Violence Prevention Strategy for the Rural Security Division of the Colombian National Police, Phase II</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The central objective of this project is to improve rural security by giving the Directorate of Carabineros and Rural Security of the Colombian National Police (DICAR, by its Spanish acronym) tools to combat drug trafficking, reduce violence, and change the culture of illegality through a strategy of community-based violence prevention in Colombia. This approach enables DICAR to strengthen trust within communities living in rural areas of the country affected by drug trafficking. The program emphasizes respect for human rights and a community-centered approach. The project also places a special emphasis on an inclusive approach, where the police and citizens work together to resolve community problems.</narrative>
  </description>
